with a path forward.

25:48.660 --> 25:50.510
<i>Yeah, uh...</i>

25:50.710 --> 25:52.640
I found somebody, too--

25:52.840 --> 25:54.640
a divorce attorney.

25:54.840 --> 25:56.340
What the hell
are you talkin' about?

25:56.540 --> 25:59.230
<i>I'm tired of the fightin',</i>
<i>Charles.</i>

25:59.430 --> 26:03.130
I don't want the kids thinkin'
that this is normal.

26:03.330 --> 26:06.110
<i>You have not been happy</i>
<i>for a long time.</i>

26:06.310 --> 26:10.530
The dirty magazines,
the lying, Mabel.

26:10.730 --> 26:13.680
<i>Truth is,</i>
<i>I haven't been happy either.</i>

26:13.880 --> 26:16.600
<i>This was not the life</i>
<i>I hoped for.</i>

26:16.800 --> 26:19.570
♪ ♪

26:24.310 --> 26:26.200
Maybe it's a good thing
I got caught.

26:26.390 --> 26:28.940
No more secrets.

26:29.140 --> 26:31.640
<i>We can start fresh.</i>

26:31.840 --> 26:33.400
God's giving us
a second chance.

26:33.600 --> 26:36.250
♪ ♪

26:36.450 --> 26:39.950
Maybe God is giving us
a second chance...

26:40.150 --> 26:41.970
just not with each other.

26:42.170 --> 26:43.630
[huffs] Lucille...

26:43.830 --> 26:46.130
♪ ♪

26:46.330 --> 26:48.630
I never imagined life
without you.

26:48.830 --> 26:51.600
♪ ♪

26:53.390 --> 26:56.000
[dog barking]

27:04.090 --> 27:06.910
[ominous music plays]

27:07.110 --> 27:10.370
♪ ♪

27:10.570 --> 27:13.190
Uh...what the fuck?

27:17.930 --> 27:19.490
No, no, no, no, no.
Wait, wai--

27:19.690 --> 27:22.420
♪ ♪

27:33.950 --> 27:35.700
Bryant.

27:35.900 --> 27:36.810
[Bryant]
What the fuck you doing here?

27:37.010 --> 27:38.570
You snooping again?

27:38.770 --> 27:40.230
Look, I know
you're hiding shit from me,

27:40.430 --> 27:42.450
but I heard the call
about Kevin on the radio,

27:42.640 --> 27:43.900
<i>and I wanted to make sure</i>
<i>you're okay.</i>

27:44.100 --> 27:45.670
What call?

27:45.870 --> 27:48.230
[siren wailing]

27:48.430 --> 27:50.530
[tires screeching]

27:52.450 --> 27:55.240
[sobbing]

27:55.440 --> 27:57.100
[car door closes]

27:58.580 --> 28:00.330
[Bryant] Stand down!

28:00.530 --> 28:02.070
Stand down!
It's my son.

28:02.270 --> 28:03.550
[officer]
All units stand down.

28:03.750 --> 28:05.510
[Bryant] My kid!

28:05.710 --> 28:08.290
[siren wailing]

28:10.900 --> 28:12.680
- [sobbing]
- Hey, uh...

28:13.730 --> 28:15.570
Hey, Kevin?

28:15.760 --> 28:17.130
- Hey, hey.
- [Kevin] Dad.

28:17.330 --> 28:20.090
- I messed up.
- [sirens continue wailing]

28:20.290 --> 28:22.680
- [Bryant] Oh, man.
- [Kevin] I'm so sorry.

28:22.880 --> 28:26.290
♪ ♪

28:26.490 --> 28:28.360
Dad, you gotta believe me when
I say that was an accident.

28:28.560 --> 28:29.880
He--he just
wouldn't leave me alone,

28:30.080 --> 28:31.410
and I didn't know
what else to do,

28:31.610 --> 28:33.060
so I got the gun
outta the safe--

28:33.260 --> 28:35.220
It's okay. Look, look,
I know it was self-defense.

28:35.410 --> 28:37.480
That's all it was, okay?
You hear me?

28:37.680 --> 28:38.980
Come on, I got you.

28:39.180 --> 28:42.090
I got you, man.

28:42.290 --> 28:43.850
It's gonna be okay.

28:44.050 --> 28:45.270
I'm right here.

28:45.470 --> 28:47.600
♪ ♪

28:47.800 --> 28:48.920
Okay.

28:49.120 --> 28:51.450
♪ ♪

28:51.650 --> 28:53.120
I love you.

28:55.250 --> 28:58.200
I'm sorry, Kevin.

28:58.390 --> 29:00.040
- What--Dad, what is she doing?
- I need you to calm down.

29:00.240 --> 29:01.480
I don't need you to talk
to anybody, you hear me?

29:01.680 --> 29:03.400
Is she arresting me?

29:03.600 --> 29:05.050
- Dad--
- Look, I don't want you to

29:05.250 --> 29:07.330
say nothing to nobody, Kevin.
You get it?

29:07.530 --> 29:08.990
- I-I said it was--
- Hey, hey.

29:09.190 --> 29:10.580
I got you.

29:10.780 --> 29:12.580
I'm gonna work this out, okay?

29:12.780 --> 29:15.100
[Kevin] Dad, I don't
wanna go to jail--please!

29:15.300 --> 29:17.740
- I said it was an accident.
- [Lin] Careful, careful.

29:17.940 --> 29:20.750
♪ ♪

29:24.360 --> 29:27.200
[dramatic musical sting]

29:27.400 --> 29:30.020
[police siren wailing]

29:37.510 --> 29:40.740
[Terry] No wonder Bryant never
came back with B-Mick's gun.

29:40.940 --> 29:42.870
Yo, Meech,
did you see this shit?

29:43.070 --> 29:45.260
Or this one.

29:45.460 --> 29:47.770
"Ninth Grader with
Nine Millimeter Murders Many."

29:47.970 --> 29:50.400
They charging Bryant's kid

29:50.600 --> 29:52.880
<i>for Jay-Mo's, Kato's, and that</i>
<i>other little kid's murder,</i>

29:53.080 --> 29:54.660
which means B-Mickie's gun
is in the clear.

29:54.860 --> 29:56.800
Yo...

29:57.000 --> 30:00.470
the eagle has fuckin' landed!

30:00.670 --> 30:01.890
And we got 500 keys?

30:02.090 --> 30:03.540
Hell, yeah.

30:03.740 --> 30:05.150
That's what the fuck
I'm talkin' about.

30:05.350 --> 30:06.720
- Everything is tied up.
- Man.

30:06.920 --> 30:08.330
Yo, B-Mickie's not,
though.

30:08.530 --> 30:10.090
Man, y'all bugging

30:10.290 --> 30:11.990
if y'all think Bryant'll
ever go down quiet,

30:12.190 --> 30:14.380
not to mention I ain't even
handled this Lamar shit yet.

30:14.580 --> 30:16.250
I got niggas all over the city
hunting that muh'fucker down.

30:16.450 --> 30:17.460
[Meech scoffs]

30:19.810 --> 30:22.260
Meech, let me holler at you
for a second.

30:22.460 --> 30:25.430
[upbeat hip-hop playing]

30:25.630 --> 30:29.070
Bro, I did not get back
in this game to lose you.

30:29.270 --> 30:30.480
What the fuck
is you talking about?

30:30.680 --> 30:32.880
We got everything we wanted.

30:33.080 --> 30:34.920
The shipment
from the Colombians--got that.

30:35.120 --> 30:36.920
Bryant's nullified.
The nigga's done.

30:37.120 --> 30:39.540
Our expansion plans
is in motion, and...

30:39.730 --> 30:42.390
Look, just let
that Lamar shit go.

30:42.590 --> 30:44.240
That motherfucker
killed Monique--

30:44.440 --> 30:45.760
the mother
of one of my kids, nigga--

30:45.960 --> 30:48.700
Nedo, Sockie, Darius.

30:48.900 --> 30:51.550
That nigga went after Nikki
and threatened Mama.

30:51.750 --> 30:53.420
Popped me and probably
popped your muh'fucking ass,

30:53.620 --> 30:55.030
and you talking
about reevaluatin'.

30:55.230 --> 30:57.600
[sighs]
Meech, we're not killers.

30:57.800 --> 30:59.210
We're businessmen.

30:59.410 --> 31:01.850
Speak for
your-motherfucking-self.

31:03.120 --> 31:04.890
[Terry sighs]

31:05.090 --> 31:07.610
♪ ♪

31:07.810 --> 31:09.830
An investigation
into your actions

31:10.030 --> 31:11.870
will be launched immediately.

31:12.070 --> 31:14.000
Hand over your gun and badge.

31:14.200 --> 31:17.440
<i>What possessed you</i>
<i>to suppress a murder weapon?</i>

31:17.640 --> 31:19.550
Look, I'ma fully cooperate.

31:19.750 --> 31:20.840
[object thuds on table]

31:21.040 --> 31:22.800
I just need to help my son.

31:23.000 --> 31:24.230
Well, you should've
thought of that

31:24.430 --> 31:26.390
before you broke the chain
of custody with that gun.

31:26.590 --> 31:30.190
I get it. Okay, so--so...

31:30.390 --> 31:33.570
what if I get Mickie to confess
to Kato and Jay-Mo?

31:33.770 --> 31:35.240
And that at least takes
those two off of Kevin.

31:35.440 --> 31:36.940
[Garr] There is no way

31:37.140 --> 31:38.860
I'm letting you anywhere near
this investigation.

31:39.060 --> 31:41.180
Look, blowback from this
is gonna be hard and fast.

31:41.380 --> 31:43.250
B-Mickie's prints
are on the gun.

31:43.450 --> 31:45.410
A confession
might soften the impact.

31:45.600 --> 31:48.100
What if I took a stab at him?

31:48.300 --> 31:51.410
All right, fine,
but on one condition.

31:51.610 --> 31:53.500
You take your ass home,

31:53.700 --> 31:55.130
and you don't talk to anyone

31:55.330 --> 31:57.300
unless it's me
or your goddamn union rep.

32:03.220 --> 32:04.920
Hey, Jin.

32:07.350 --> 32:10.040
- Thanks for stepping up.
- Fuck you.

32:10.240 --> 32:13.500
I'm doing this for Kevin,
not your trifling ass.

32:13.700 --> 32:16.460
[dark music plays]

32:16.660 --> 32:18.420
[knock at door]

32:18.620 --> 32:20.330
<i>It's Detective Jin.</i>
<i>I'm alone.</i>

32:20.530 --> 32:21.720
<i>Brian, I know you're in there.</i>
<i>Open up.</i>

32:21.920 --> 32:23.460
<i>- Come on, open up.</i>
- [knock at door]

32:25.940 --> 32:27.300
[B-Mickie]
What the fuck do you want, man?

32:27.490 --> 32:29.430
I ain't got shit to say
to no crooked-ass cop.

32:29.630 --> 32:31.520
I know that Bryant was holding
that gun over your head

32:31.720 --> 32:33.430
and that you broke
into his house to get it.

32:33.630 --> 32:35.910
<i>And I'm sorry that he moved</i>

32:36.110 --> 32:38.920
your mother into that shitty
hospital before she died.

32:39.120 --> 32:41.350
None of that shit
will bring her back.

32:41.550 --> 32:45.180
Look, what Bryant did
was fucked up.

32:45.380 --> 32:47.620
But they have the gun now.

32:47.820 --> 32:49.230
And once they connect the dots,

32:49.430 --> 32:51.970
you're gonna be facing
multiple life sentences.

32:52.170 --> 32:55.710
Now, if you confess,
I can try to get you less time.

32:55.910 --> 32:57.800
And when you're out,

32:58.000 --> 33:00.890
we'll put you somewhere safe
for a fresh start.

33:01.090 --> 33:03.680
[dramatic music plays]

33:03.880 --> 33:05.590
I'd be in cuffs by now if y'all
really had shit on me.

33:05.790 --> 33:06.730
You know that, right?

33:06.930 --> 33:08.180
Bluffing-ass bitch.

33:08.380 --> 33:11.160
♪ ♪

33:22.950 --> 33:25.680
[ominous chords]

33:25.880 --> 33:28.170
♪ ♪

33:37.400 --> 33:38.890
[footsteps approaching]

33:39.090 --> 33:40.790
[gun cocks]

33:45.840 --> 33:48.770
[Lamar] <i>Looks like the rabbit</i>
<i>finally caught the wolf, huh?</i>

33:48.970 --> 33:50.630
Go ahead, then, shit.

33:52.760 --> 33:55.300
I'll send your regards
to Monique--go on.

33:55.500 --> 33:57.990
This for all the fire
you hailed down on us.

33:58.190 --> 34:00.060
But, most importantly,
this is for me.

34:00.260 --> 34:02.480
♪ ♪

34:02.680 --> 34:04.430
I'm the nigga stopped you dead
in your tracks.

34:06.430 --> 34:09.050
See, you learned something.

34:09.250 --> 34:11.010
In order to take down
the Devil,

34:11.210 --> 34:13.920
you gotta go
down to hell with him.

34:14.120 --> 34:16.140
I'ma keep your seat warm
for you.

34:16.340 --> 34:17.880
Go on, bitch.

34:18.080 --> 34:20.340
You twisted fuck.

34:20.540 --> 34:22.760
This what you want, huh?

34:22.960 --> 34:24.670
You don't deserve
the easy way out.

34:24.870 --> 34:27.330
Nigga, nothin' in my life
ever been easy.

34:27.530 --> 34:31.180
Why the fuck
would I put your sorry ass

34:31.380 --> 34:33.160
out your misery

34:33.360 --> 34:34.770
when I could just watch
you suffer?

34:34.970 --> 34:36.750
[scoffs, grunts]

34:36.950 --> 34:39.380
♪ ♪

34:39.580 --> 34:40.820
You see this?

34:41.020 --> 34:44.080
This gonna feel like a noose.

34:44.280 --> 34:47.170
It's gonna get tighter and
tighter every day on your neck

34:47.370 --> 34:48.630
until you can't fucking breathe
no more.

34:48.830 --> 34:50.830
♪ ♪

34:51.030 --> 34:53.070
Go on, bitch.

34:53.270 --> 34:56.000
♪ ♪

34:57.650 --> 35:00.380
- [chuckles]
- [Meech] <i>Smoke that shit.</i>

35:00.580 --> 35:03.300
[chuckles, sighs]

35:03.500 --> 35:05.670
♪ ♪

35:05.870 --> 35:08.140
[inhaling]

35:14.580 --> 35:17.530
[groans contentedly]

35:17.730 --> 35:20.460
♪ ♪

35:23.110 --> 35:25.860
Keep feeding his ass
so we can keep him this way.

35:28.770 --> 35:30.730
I threw a little extra
in there, too, for your help.

35:44.180 --> 35:45.180
[door opens]

35:47.750 --> 35:48.490
[door closes]

35:54.280 --> 35:57.290
[ambient background noise]

35:57.490 --> 36:00.140
[soft music playing]

36:00.340 --> 36:03.070
♪ ♪

36:04.590 --> 36:06.730
[door opens]

36:06.930 --> 36:08.550
The hell you cheesing about?

36:12.510 --> 36:14.980
I took care of Lamar's bitch
ass just the way you wanted.

36:15.180 --> 36:16.700
Yeah?

36:16.900 --> 36:18.530
Look, man, I ain't gonna lie.
You was right.

36:18.730 --> 36:20.090
There was a better way.

36:20.290 --> 36:21.460
But now I'm asking you

36:21.660 --> 36:23.100
to respect the way
I handle B-Mick.

36:23.300 --> 36:24.710
Now I know something's up.
What's up?

36:24.910 --> 36:26.530
[exhales deeply]

36:26.730 --> 36:27.790
All right, look...

36:30.010 --> 36:31.930
It's time for us to take
this show on the road, Tee,

36:32.130 --> 36:33.610
and head back down south.

36:33.810 --> 36:36.520
[chuckles] Wait, wait.
I don't--I don't understand.

36:36.720 --> 36:38.500
You just said
we got rid of Lamar.

36:38.700 --> 36:40.070
Everything's done.
The streets is bleeding BMF.

36:40.270 --> 36:41.790
I want more.

36:41.990 --> 36:43.420
With the work coming in
from Florida,

36:43.620 --> 36:45.590
I'll be closer to the source.

36:47.330 --> 36:48.560
What happened
to womb to the tomb?

36:48.760 --> 36:50.170
[Meech] <i>We men now, Tee.</i>

36:50.370 --> 36:51.470
<i>Now, it's impossible</i>

36:51.670 --> 36:53.300
for us to run a crew
from the same city

36:53.500 --> 36:55.170
without stepping
on each other's toes.

36:55.370 --> 36:58.700
Besides, this how
we about to blow up.

36:58.900 --> 37:02.440
So you begged me to come back
so we could end shit like this?

37:02.640 --> 37:04.750
We not ending
a motherfucking thing.

37:04.950 --> 37:06.180
<i>Just changin'.</i>

37:06.380 --> 37:08.530
With me running distro
out of ATL

37:08.730 --> 37:11.170
and you still holding shit down
as king of the D,

37:11.370 --> 37:12.670
we'll still be
womb to the tomb,

37:12.870 --> 37:14.360
just 700 miles apart.

37:14.560 --> 37:17.080
700 miles apart, huh?

37:17.280 --> 37:20.060
♪ ♪

37:21.410 --> 37:23.590
[Meech] <i>And...</i>

37:23.790 --> 37:26.380
nigga, I'm about to throw the
biggest going-away party ever.

37:26.580 --> 37:28.490
I'm talking about the biggest
shit niggas ever seen,

37:28.690 --> 37:30.050
and they gonna be talkin'
about it for years.

37:30.250 --> 37:32.560
Yeah, I don't doubt that.

37:32.760 --> 37:34.170
You know I'm still not over
this B-Mickie shit,

37:34.370 --> 37:35.890
though, right?

37:36.090 --> 37:38.020
[rapper] <i>♪ My Adidas ♪</i>

37:38.220 --> 37:39.590
<i>♪ Walk through concert doors ♪</i>

37:39.790 --> 37:42.540
<i>♪ And roam</i>
<i>All over coliseum floors ♪</i>

37:42.740 --> 37:44.980
<i>♪ I stepped onstage</i>
<i>At Live Aid ♪</i>

37:45.180 --> 37:47.550
<i>♪ All the people gave</i>
<i>And the poor got paid ♪</i>

37:47.750 --> 37:49.990
<i>♪ And out of speakers</i>
<i>I did speak ♪</i>

37:50.190 --> 37:52.510
<i>♪ I wore my sneakers</i>
<i>But I'm not a sneak ♪</i>

37:52.710 --> 37:54.990
<i>♪ My Adidas touch the sand</i>
<i>Of a foreign land ♪</i>

37:55.190 --> 37:58.410
<i>♪ With mic in hand</i>
<i>I cold took command ♪</i>

37:58.610 --> 38:00.430
What's up, boy? You want to get
one of these Polish dogs?

38:00.630 --> 38:03.370
Now, you know I'll never say no
to no hot food.

38:03.570 --> 38:04.720
[chuckles]
That's how I know you my son.

38:04.920 --> 38:06.020
[both laugh]

38:06.220 --> 38:08.810
Hey, um, look, Pops...

38:09.010 --> 38:10.590
whatever happened
with you and Ma,

38:10.790 --> 38:13.030
just--just know I-I always want
you in my kids' life

38:13.230 --> 38:16.320
and mine's, too,
so don't even sweat it.

38:16.520 --> 38:19.340
♪ ♪

38:19.540 --> 38:21.430
[Charles]
Uh-oh, what you up to now?

38:21.630 --> 38:23.650
Just thinking about that glow
on your face

38:23.850 --> 38:25.260
when me and you used to jam
in the church band together.

38:25.460 --> 38:27.520
[chuckles] We did tear it up.

38:27.720 --> 38:29.530
I'm surprised
your heathen behind remembers.

38:29.730 --> 38:31.420
After all the sacrifices
you made, Pops,

38:31.620 --> 38:33.010
<i>especially for our family,</i>

38:33.210 --> 38:35.270
putting up with me, Tee,
Nikki, and Mama,

38:35.470 --> 38:36.750
it's the least I could do.

38:36.950 --> 38:38.190
[Terry] Ooh.

38:38.390 --> 38:39.970
Yo, that's dope.

38:40.170 --> 38:42.000
I hope you like it.

38:42.190 --> 38:43.240
Love you, Meech.

38:43.440 --> 38:44.670
I love you, too, Pops.

38:44.870 --> 38:47.490
[indistinct chatter]

38:50.320 --> 38:52.850
- [Charles] Well I'll be damned.
- [Meech] Uh-uh.

38:53.050 --> 38:55.050
A wanderin' eye's what got you
in trouble the first time.

38:55.250 --> 38:57.380
- [Charles chuckles]
- Oh, my--

38:57.580 --> 38:59.990
Ma?

39:00.190 --> 39:01.950
Which one of y'all's
gonna dance with me?

39:02.150 --> 39:03.820
That's gonna be me.

39:04.020 --> 39:06.080
[indistinct chatter]

39:06.280 --> 39:09.020
[upbeat dance music playing]

39:09.220 --> 39:11.220
♪ ♪

39:11.420 --> 39:12.790
[Lucille] Come on, baby.
Show me what you got.

39:12.990 --> 39:14.720
[giggling]

39:14.920 --> 39:17.610
♪ ♪

39:30.060 --> 39:32.370
I ain't get no invite,
so I really wasn't sure.

39:32.570 --> 39:33.850
<i>Shit.</i>

39:34.050 --> 39:35.940
You're not
a part of this no more.

39:36.140 --> 39:37.030
What the fuck
are you talkin' about?

39:37.230 --> 39:38.760
You my brother, B.

39:40.460 --> 39:42.400
